Exercise 2: Load Country from Spring Configuration XML
ðŸ“„ Description:
This exercise demonstrates how to configure a Spring bean using an XML file and load it using ClassPathXmlApplicationContext. A Country object is defined in beans.xml and retrieved in a Java application.
ðŸ§ª Sample Input:
(Defined in beans.xml)

<bean id="country" class="com.example.demo.Country">
    <property name="name" value="India"/>
    <property name="capital" value="New Delhi"/>
</bean>

ðŸ“¤ Sample Output (from console):

Country Name: India  
Capital: New Delhi

ðŸ›  Used Components:
Spring Core (org.springframework.context)

ClassPathXmlApplicationContext to load XML configuration

Java class Country.java with standard getters, setters, and toString()
